<HEADLINE>
<P>
UCLA PLAYS GERMAN TEAM TONIGHT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By JERRY CROWE 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
UCLA, in its final tuneup before Friday night's season opener against UC Irvine 
in the Great Alaska Shootout, will play TTL Bamberg, a German club team, in an 
exhibition game tonight at 7:30 at Pauley Pavilion. 
</P>
<P>
TTL Bamberg, coached by former Bruin Terry Schofield, is 0-6 on its U.S. tour, 
and has lost at Arizona and Arizona State. 
</P>
<P>
The UCLA women's team will play the Bulgarian national team in a preliminary 
game at 5:15. JERRY CROWE 
</P>
</TEXT>
