<HEADLINE>
<P>
CHARLINE CHABLE ROTONDO; WON MEDAL OF FREEDOM 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Charline Chable Rotondo, 78, a member of the French underground who was honored 
with the Medal of Freedom for helping save American fliers from the Nazis. She 
was the first foreign-born woman to receive the Medal of Freedom, America's 
highest civilian honor. Her exploits in the French underground saved 32 
American fliers from the Nazis during World War II. Gen. Dwight D. Eisenhower 
presented the medal in Paris in 1945, after Rotondo escaped from the Germans, 
who tortured and imprisoned her. She moved to the United States in 1974 and 
died of lung cancer on Thursday in Concord, N.H. 
</P>
</TEXT>
