<HEADLINE>
<P>
SEN. JESSE HELMS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Thanks to Huntington Williams (Opinion, Nov. 11), we now understand Sen. Jesse 
Helms (R-N.C.). 
</P>
<P>
First, Helms wants to limit the power of government except for pork-barrel 
items for his state and government policies which encourage school 
resegregation. 
</P>
<P>
Second, Helms believes in the sanctity of private property except for women. 
Third, Helms believes in individual responsibility and so wants to abrogate 
social safety net programs, thus allowing those now covered to fall by the 
wayside. Fourth, Helms believes in charities except for endowments to the arts 
and to charities servicing those with a lesser right-wing tilt, using his 
perspective. Williams says that Helms represents a large and growing 
constituency that extends beyond North Carolina. No wonder the country is in 
trouble. 
</P>
<P>
BOB BUTLER, Culver City 
</P>
