<HEADLINE>
<P>
BUCHANAN ON IRAQ CRISIS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
As a perennial Buchanan-basher I never dreamed I would be writing this letter 
in his favor. 
</P>
<P>
But I am delighted! Not with his every word of course, but with his general 
conclusions. 
</P>
<P>
In our last two wars in Korea and Vietnam, we wasted thousands of lives first 
and then we sat down and talked for thousands of hours. Why don't we reverse 
the procedure for this one? Let us talk with the "madman" for as long as it 
takes, even while he's in Kuwait. I don't think the future dead will mind the 
delay a bit. 
</P>
<P>
Talk is cheap; it's our children's lives that are expensive. 
</P>
<P>
BURTON HENRY, Temecula 
</P>
</TEXT>
