<HEADLINE>
<P>
WORLD IN BRIEF; 
</P>
<P>
DOMINICAN REPUBLIC; 
</P>
<P>
STRIKERS PROTEST AUSTERITY PROGRAM 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Staff and Wire Reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Dominicans angry over the government's economic austerity program paralyzed 
much of the country on the first day of a three-day general strike. Seven 
people were reported wounded in clashes and bombings, and about 100 protesters 
were arrested. Schools and businesses were closed, and thousands of people were 
without public transportation. 
</P>
</TEXT>
