<HEADLINE>
<P>
METRO DIGEST / LOCAL NEWS IN BRIEF: HEARING DELAYED FOR FAN IN ASSAULT CASE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A preliminary hearing for the Los Angeles Raiders fan who allegedly attacked 
and seriously injured a Pittsburgh Steelers fan during a game between the two 
teams at the Coliseum on Sept. 23 was continued until Dec. 10 following a 
request by the defense attorney for more time. 
</P>
<P>
Shane C. Geringer, 19, of Agoura Hills, has pleaded not guilty to one count 
each of assault with a deadly weapon and battery causing serious bodily injury, 
both felonies. 
</P>
<P>
Geringer's attorney, Leslie Abramson, told Municipal Court Judge Alban Niles 
she needed time to study the medical records of the victim, Paul Albrecht, 35, 
of Tucson, Ariz., and to talk to witnesses. 
</P>
<P>
Deputy Dist. Atty. Craig Veals had more than a dozen witnesses ready to 
testify. 
</P>
</TEXT>
<GRAPHIC>
<P>
Photo, Shane Geringer 
</P>
