<HEADLINE>
<P>
REGIONAL ROUNDUP: GROVE SHOPPING CENTER SOLD FOR $26 MILLION 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The Grove, a 9.4-acre shopping center in Northridge, was sold to retail 
developer Golden West Properties of Beverly Hills for about $26 million. 
</P>
<P>
The deal was announced by Wells Fargo Realty Finance, which represented the 
seller, Walnut Grove Associates Ltd. of Farmington, Conn., and previously 
arranged financing to build and later rehabilitate the shopping center. 
</P>
<P>
The center is at the corner of Tampa Avenue and Nordhoff Street and includes 
Marshalls, Pier 1 Imports and The Good Guys stores. 
</P>
</TEXT>
