<HEADLINE>
<P>
REGIONAL EARNINGS: PERFECTDATA'S PROFITS CLIMB TO $139,000 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PerfectData Corp., a Simi Valley maker of maintenance supplies for computer 
equipment, reported earnings of $139,000 in the fiscal second quarter that 
ended Sept. 30, contrasted with $3,000 in net income a year earlier. 
</P>
<P>
Revenues rose 49% to $1.41 million from $946,000. 
</P>
<P>
For the six months that ended Sept. 30, the company earned $277,000, as 
revenues jumped 65% to $2.83 million. In the same period a year before, it 
earned $3,000 on revenues of $1.72 million. 
</P>
<P>
PerfectData attributed the improved results to its expansion into new markets, 
new product development and enhancement of existing products. 
</P>
</TEXT>
