<P>
HOLIDAY RUSH: Sheriff Brad Gates, trying to keep the jail population within 
court-ordered limits, has asked local judges to forsake a longstanding holiday 
tradition. . . . Reluctant to lock up less serious prisoners over the holidays, 
judges typically stay sentences until Jan. 2. The result: up to 1,000 people 
lining up for booking on the day after New Year's. . . . Gates is asking that 
the rush be spread over four to six weeks, and Superior Court Presiding Judge 
Leonard Goldstein says judges will try to cooperate. Jim Newton and Jerry Hicks 
