</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
OLD SOLDIERS: After running for district attorney against his boss, Michael R. 
Capizzi, and then losing, Chief Deputy D.A. James G. Enright, 64, started his 
vacation Monday and will not return. . . . When his vacation ends, Enright will 
retire after 30 years in the D.A.'s office. . . . Any parting words? No, says 
