<HEADLINE>
<P>
WHAT WORLD LEADERS SAID 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
'The Continent, frozen in hostility for so long, has become a Continent of 
revolutionary change.' 
</P>
<P>
GEORGE BUSH 
</P>
<P>
U.S. President 
</P>
<P>
'Our meeting takes place at the turning point of two eras. It constitutes a 
major event. Its consequences will be felt for centuries.' 
</P>
<P>
MIKHAIL S. GORBACHEV 
</P>
<P>
Soviet president 
</P>
<P>
'There would be no summit today . . . had it not been for the . . . conviction 
of President Gorbachev that the desire for peace lives in the hearts and minds 
of all men and all women.' 
</P>
<P>
BRIAN MULRONEY 
</P>
<P>
Canadian prime minister 
</P>
</TEXT>
