<P>
ORANGE COUNTY FOCUS: LA PALMA; 
</P>
<P>
WRITE-IN CANDIDATE LOSES IN COUNCIL BID 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By LYNDA NATALI 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
With all absentee votes tallied, write-in candidate Wally Linn fell short in 
his bid for City Council. 
</P>
<P>
Incumbents Larry A. Herman and Orbrey Duke were able to fend off Linn, who 
received only 571 votes. Linn, a real estate broker, finished fifth behind 
challengers Christian Basquette and Kenneth Tipton. The candidates were 
competing for two four-year terms. 
</P>
<P>
Herman and Duke, who were ahead after the original counts, maintained their 
strong leads. In the final tally, Duke received 2,276 votes and Herman received 
2,134. 
</P>
<P>
Linn entered the race on the last possible day and campaigned hard in the weeks 
before the election. However, because he was a write-in candidate, his name did 
not appear on the ballot. LYNDA NATALI 
</P>
</TEXT>
