<HEADLINE>
<P>
ORANGE COUNTY EARNINGS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Vestro Foods Inc.: The Newport Beach specialty-food company reported 
third-quarter earnings of $24,000, including a one-time charge of $116,000 from 
a change in estimated tax liability, contrasted with a loss of $7,000 in the 
year-earlier quarter. 
</P>
<P>
Sales rose to $8.8 million from $4.1 million. For the nine-month period, 
earnings increased to $182,000 from $168,000 in the prior year. Sales rose 83%, 
to $24.1 million from $13.2 million. Alfred Strogoff, president and chief 
executive, attributed the sales increase primarily to acquisitions. 
</P>
</TEXT>
