<TEXT>
<P>
Three current or former Oklahoma State baseball players were in satisfactory 
condition after a car accident that killed a Pawhuska, Okla., man who was 
driving the vehicle. 
</P>
<P>
Thomas Barry Carter, a longtime supporter of the team, died when he lost 
control of the car, the Oklahoma Highway Patrol said. 
</P>
<P>
Derek Brandow and Ritchie Moody, sophomore pitchers for the Cowboys who played 
in last season's College World Series, and Eric Coca, a former third baseman, 
were in satisfactory condition at St. Joseph Medical Center in Ponca City, 
hospital officials said. 
</P>
