<HEADLINE>
<P>
THE SIDELINES; 
</P>
<P>
GIRL CAGER DIES DURING PRACTICE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
DANBURY, Conn. 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A female high school basketball player who became ill during a practice session 
collapsed and died as she was being led out of a gymnasium. Her brother also 
died as a high school athlete. 
</P>
<P>
Patty LiVolsi, 16, a junior at Immaculate High School, collapsed in a hallway 
Monday evening moments after she told an assistant coach she was feeling 
nauseous, Coach Joseph Appello said. 
</P>
<P>
She was pronounced dead at Danbury Hospital. The State Medical Examiner's 
Office in Farmington performed an autopsy today, but released no information 
pending further study. 
</P>
<P>
LiVolsi's older brother, Greg, died several years ago of a heart condition 
while he was in high school, said Appello. He was a football and basketball 
player. 
</P>
<P>
The team has dedicated the basketball season to LiVolsi. 
</P>
<P>
Father Robert Post, principal of Immaculate, said LiVolsi had had a physical 
before the school year began. 
</P>
<P>
"I read her physical this morning, and there was nothing to indicate that there 
was any disorder," Post said today. 
</P>
<P>
Post said he did not know whether LiVolsi had ever been tested for a heart 
condition like her brother's, but said he knew of no previous incidents when 
she had felt ill before a game. 
</P>
</TEXT>
