<P>
NEWMAN AIDS MS. COLLEGE PLAN 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Wire Services 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
NEW YORK 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Paul Newman is donating $10,000 from his Newman's Own line of food products to 
help keep a Ms. magazine educational program cooking. 
</P>
<P>
The program, "Ms.: the World of Women," provides copies of the magazine for use 
in women's, sociology and psychology classes at about 2,000 U.S. colleges. 
</P>
<P>
The magazine initially provided the copies free. After Ms. ran into financial 
troubles last year, people such as Newman began underwriting the program, 
publisher Ruth Bower said. 
</P>
<P>
Newman's company donates its earnings from such products as salad dressing to 
charity. 
</P>
</TEXT>
