<P>
TRUMP IN VIDEO ROLE FOR CHARITY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Wire Services 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Donald Trump plays a featured role in the new video for all-female hard rock 
band Precious Metal, portraying the title character for the song "Mr. Big 
Stuff," Chameleon Records announced Monday. 
</P>
<P>
Trump has agreed to donate to charity the $25,000 performance fee paid to him 
by the record company, plus $50,000 if the record goes gold and an additional 
$150,000 if it goes platinum. 
</P>
<P>
Although it is the second rock video appearance for the famed financier, it 
marks his first feature role. He had a walk-through in a Bobby Brown video. 
</P>
<P>
Precious Metal vocalist Leslie Knauer said The Donald was "a real gentleman to 
work with, very patient . . . and he takes great direction." 
</P>
<P>
"Mr. Big Stuff" is a remake of the 1971 Jean Knight classic. 
</P>
</TEXT>
