<P>
AXL ROSE ASKS RESTRAINING ORDER 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Wire Services 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Singer Axl Rose, facing possible assault charges for allegedly beating his 
neighbor, asked Monday for a restraining order against her, claiming she is a 
"potentially dangerous rock-and-roll 'groupie.' 
</P>
<P>
" 
</P>
<P>
The 28-year-old lead singer of the heavy metal band Guns N' Roses wants a Los 
Angeles Superior Court judge to bar Gabriella Kantor from any contact with him, 
his wife, Erin, or any visitors to their West Hollywood condominium. 
</P>
<P>
Rose was arrested Oct. 30, after Kantor called the Sheriff's Department and 
accused the singer of hitting her on the head with a wine bottle. The alleged 
assault occurred about 2:30 a.m., outside Rose's residence in the 8700 block of 
Shoreham Drive West. 
</P>
</TEXT>
<GRAPHIC>
<P>
Photo, Axl Rose 
</P>
